'I think it's very exciting for both of us, and also for fans, to see a rematch of the great final from last year,' Federer, who lost to the Serbian in three sets in the Californian desert back in 2014, told bnpparibasopen.com.

'I'm looking forward to it, and I hope I can keep up my good play.'

Federer earned a break point in the fifth game but Raonic saved it with an ace before holding. The Swiss soon broke for a 6-5 lead and wrapped up the set.

The 33-year-old opened the second set with a break to consolidate his lead and went on to endure nine aces before saving a break point to claim victory inside 86 minutes.

